        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 4:42PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 442 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from 6 miles southwest of Caroga Lake Public Campground to
near Ephratah to near Cherry Valley. Movement was east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Meco, Charleston, West Perth, Fultonville, Johnstown, Young Corners,
Hale Mills, North Broadalbin, McKinley, Yosts, Manny Corners, Union
Mills, Red Bunch Corners, Fort Johnson, Hill Corners, Gloversville,
Dennies Hollow, Green Corners, Bergen Park, and Auriesville.

This includes Interstate 90 between exits 27 and 29.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
eastern and east central New York.</instruction>
